OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"His intention was to break into Mr
OL,8,FPerks' house, set fire to it and, if
OL,9,Fnecessary, stab Mr Perks."
OL,11,FOpening the case on Monday, Ms Ayling
OL,12,Ftold the court: "His intention was,
OL,13,Fsay the Crown, to break into Mr Perks'
OL,14,Fhouse, set fire to it and, if
OL,15,Fnecessary, stab Mr Perks.
OL,17,F"In short, the Crown say he intended
OL,18,Fto kill Mr Perks by either of those
OL,19,Fmeans ` the use of fire or the use of
OL,20,Fthe knife."
