OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMs Ayling said: "The prosecution does
OL,8,Fnot have to prove a motive for any
OL,9,Fcrime, however, it is clear that the
OL,10,Fdefendant hated Graeme Perks.
OL,12,F"Mr Perks was asleep in bed and heard
OL,13,Fa loud noise in the early hours of the
OL,14,Fmorning. He got out of bed... and ran
OL,15,Fdownstairs and into the drawing room.
OL,17,F"Mr Perks said to police afterwards
OL,18,Fthat he thought he smelt something
OL,19,Funusual and his feet felt a bit damp."
