OL,7,FMr Justice Pepperall told the jury the
OL,8,Fdefendant will not be in court for his
OL,9,Ftrial - which is expected to last 14
OL,10,Fweeks.
OL,12,FHe said: "The fact he is not here does
OL,13,Fnot affect your task which is to
OL,14,Fdecide whether he is guilty of the
OL,15,Fcharges against him.
OL,17,F"You must not speculate about the
OL,18,Freason Dr Brooks is not here ` his
OL,19,Fabsence is not evidence against him
OL,20,Fand must not affect your judgment.
